			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: TWINKING A BARD ~ 400k ~ Suggestions<a name="46509"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jun 16 04 7:51 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Hola-
<br />

<br />
I've been twinking a bard up for, oh, a year or three now, below are some observations I've made.  Also, you might want to consider spending the $12/year for majelo access to use the advanced search (there's something similar w/ allakhazams too I think, but a bit more expensive iirc).  Helps a bunch doing comparisons w/ weighted values.  Here's a link to my twink:  
<br />
<a target="_new" href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=383608">http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=383608</a>
<br />

<br />
very low levels (0-20):
<br />
-banded or acrylia armor, store bought instruments (combine stuff is good, from katta or seru).  Start with beginner HP jewelry and perhaps a djarnn's ring.  If you hate twisting or playing a bard, no big loss in pp.<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" />
<br />

<br />
at lower levels (20 to 40 or so):
<br />
-hp regen (fungi tunic or iksar bp).
<br />

<br />
-weapons: wavecrasher is a fantastic twink weapon (procs at level 5 or lower, slow + dot).  There's a literal ton of good bard 1hs/b/p weapons to choose from, you'll probably want a troub mace at some point.  There's also a good piercer from LoY with an instrument mod, but it's got a recommended level iirc.
<br />

<br />
-AC/HP gear, get to 900ish+ AC with all tradeable gear.  Tradeskill armor and jewelry is great stuff at those levels- cheap, typically doesn't have req'd level, and tradeable.  Lodi shield for back is good choice imho.  Steelweave (erud cultural armor) is pretty cheap and very good AC.  Less expensive is acrylia plate.
<br />

<br />
-get good instruments; TDoK, immaculate shell horn, flute of sacred glade, lute of the howler and you are good until it's epic time (min level for epic is 50).  
<br />

<br />
-clicky stuff.  Some of the clicky kunark armor (singing steel boots for lev, bracer for DS, helmet for eye of zomm) are things you'll use for awhile.  boots of the mosquito or goblin ring for invis to break charms.  Lodi boots for an AC self buff if you aren't 2 boxing or getting twinked.
<br />

<br />
-haste; I'd shoot for something in the 20-30pct range unless you have spare pp for a 36% item.  Definitely a discressionary purchase.  There's an earring (quested) from GoD with ~20% haste + good stats that might work well.
<br />

<br />
-jboots.  buy the MQ for em, should be cheap and it's just nice for a lower level toon to have a non-spell movement speed buff (unless you prefer sow potions).
<br />

<br />
40-60:
<br />
-singing steel bp for hp regen if you like swarming/kiting.  Battledrummer piercer for percussion mod'ed weapon (unless you finish your epic).  *Lots* of good required/recommended level PoP and GoD drops and tradeskill items.  Start saving/collecting for ornate molds (min level 55?).
<br />

<br />
Have fun!
<br />

<br />
RdT.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
